This paper deals with the problem of noisy labels in vision datasets and proposes a new regularization method for learning robust classifiers. The paper discusses the use of adversarial regularization in the context of label noise, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the effectiveness of the proposed method on five datasets, which suggests that it could be relevant to the sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
